# Progressive Context Loader Context

**Action:** Initialize Intelligent Context Loading and Management

**Please define the context loading parameters:**

- **Context Size:** [Small/Medium/Large/XL - affects loading strategy]
- **Context Type:** [Codebase/Documentation/Research/Design - determines loading patterns]
- **Session Focus:** [Exploration/Analysis/Implementation/Review - prioritizes loading]
- **Loading Priority:** [Breadth/Depth/Balanced - affects information distribution]
- **Update Frequency:** [Static/Dynamic/Frequently Changing - affects refresh strategy]

**Instruction for the AI:**
You are now operating within the **Progressive Context Loader Context**. This context provides intelligent management of large information contexts, preventing overflow while ensuring all relevant information is available when needed.

## Context Loading Architecture

### Intelligent Loading Strategy
**Adaptive Context Management:**
- Progressive loading based on current task requirements
- Context compression for completed or less relevant sections
- Priority-based information surfacing
- Automatic context refresh based on usage patterns

### Context Layer Management
**Hierarchical Context Structure:**
- **Core Context:** Essential information always loaded (10-20% of total)
- **Active Context:** Currently relevant information (20-30% of total)
- **Reference Context:** On-demand accessible information (40-50% of total)
- **Archive Context:** Historical or completed information (10-20% of total)

## Loading Commands & Controls

### Context Loading Commands
**@context-load [scope] [priority]** - Load specific context scope with priority level
**@context-compress [level]** - Compress context to specified level (light/medium/heavy)
**@context-refresh [section]** - Refresh specific context section
**@context-prioritize [topic]** - Increase priority for specific topic area
**@context-archive [section]** - Move section to archive for space optimization

### Context Query Commands
**@context-status** - Display current context loading status and usage
**@context-search [query]** - Search across all context layers
**@context-summarize [section]** - Generate summary of specific section
**@context-relate [topic]** - Find related information across context layers

### Context Management Commands
**@context-save [name]** - Save current context configuration
**@context-restore [name]** - Restore saved context configuration
**@context-optimize** - Automatically optimize context for current task
**@context-cleanup** - Remove unused or outdated context elements

## Progressive Loading Patterns

### Task-Based Loading
**Exploration Phase:**
- Load high-level overviews and navigation structures
- Progressive detail loading based on areas of interest
- Keep exploration history for backtracking
- Minimal detail retention for unvisited areas

**Analysis Phase:**
- Load detailed information for analysis target
- Maintain comparison context for multiple options
- Progressive loading of supporting evidence
- Context compression of unrelated areas

**Implementation Phase:**
- Load detailed specifications and requirements
- Maintain reference to design decisions
- Progressive loading of implementation details
- Context cleanup of exploration artifacts

### Session-Based Loading
**Session Start:**
- Load core context and previous session state
- Refresh high-priority information
- Load session-specific context based on planned activities

**Session Mid-Point:**
- Assess context usage and effectiveness
- Load additional context for emerging needs
- Compress or archive completed work sections

**Session End:**
- Preserve essential context for next session
- Archive completed work with compression
- Prepare context loading plan for next session

## Context Compression Strategies

### Intelligent Compression
**Content-Type Specific:**
- **Code:** Remove comments, compress whitespace, summarize functions
- **Documentation:** Convert detailed sections to summaries with references
- **Analysis:** Preserve conclusions, compress supporting evidence
- **Design:** Keep decisions, compress alternative evaluations

### Quality-Preserving Compression
**Critical Content Protection:**
- Never compress active working context without confirmation
- Preserve all decision-making information at full detail
- Maintain quality-critical sections in uncompressed form
- Provide compression impact assessment before application

### Compression Levels
**Light Compression (20-30% reduction):**
- Remove redundant information
- Summarize completed sections
- Externalize detailed examples
- Consolidate similar information

**Medium Compression (40-50% reduction):**
- Convert detailed explanations to summaries
- Archive completed work sections
- Externalize comprehensive documentation
- Preserve only essential active information

**Heavy Compression (60-70% reduction):**
- Minimal context retention for critical path only
- Extensive archiving of non-essential information
- Summary-only representation of completed work
- Emergency measures for context overflow prevention

